    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Creative works, usually two-dimensional, depicting an outdoor scene dominated by the land, hills, fields, sky, trees, fields, rivers or other bodies of water, and other natural elements. Landscapes may include a near point of view in the foreground, but also usually depict a view into the distance. Landscapes may contain architecture or figures, but the primary focus remains the land. When an ocean, sea, or other large body of water dominates the picture, use "seascapes." For actual areas of land rather than depictions, use "landscapes (environments)."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079228/Grove Art Online (2008-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000045405/Janson, History of Art (1997)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Úsese para obras creativas que representan escenas de exteriores en donde la pintura es dominada por la configuración, visual y estética, de la tierra, masas de agua, y elementos naturales. Cuando el océano u otra masa de agua de mayor tamaño domina la imagen, use "paisaje marino". Para imágenes que son más documentales que creativas, prefiera "vista" o "vista topográfica". Para áreas de terreno actuales que tienen ciertas características notables, use "paisaje (ambiente)".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Beeldende werken waarvan de hoofdvoorstelling de landelijke omgeving is. Gebruik 'zeegezichten' voor beeldende werken met als hoofdvoorstelling de zee. Gebruik 'gezichten' of 'topografische aanzichten' wanneer benadrukt wordt dat het om voorstellingen gaat van werkelijk bestaande omgevingen of objecten, vanuit één standpunt vastgelegd.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099099/Van Dale groot woordenboek (1994)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>描繪戶外場景、畫面主要為以視覺及美學手法將土地、河川海洋及自然元素融會配置而成的創造性作品。「海景繪畫」是指畫面以海洋或其他大河川為主的繪畫，「景觀(環境)」則是指具有某種令人矚目的特色之土地實景。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Schöpferisches Werk, gewöhnlich zweidimensional, das eine Ansicht im Freien darstellt, die von Boden, Hügeln, Feldern, Himmel, Bäumen, Flüssen oder anderen Gewässern und Naturelementen bestimmt ist. Landschaften können einen nahen Blickpunkt im Vordergrund enthalten, aber zeigen gewöhnlich auch einen Blick in die Ferne. Landschaften können Architektur oder Figuren enthalten, aber der haupsächliche Schwerpunkt bleibt das Land. Für eine Landschaftsdarstellung, in der ein Ozean, das Meer oder andere große Gewässer das Bild bestimmen, siehe ["Seestück"](300117546). Für eine tatsächliche Landfläche statt einer Darstellung siehe ["Landschaft (Lebensraum)"](300008626).</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Trabalhos criativos, geralmente bidimensionais, representando uma cena ao ar livre dominada pela terra, colinas, campos, céu, árvores, campos, rios ou outros corpos d'água e outros elementos naturais. As paisagens podem incluir um ponto de vista próximo em primeiro plano, mas geralmente também representam uma vista ao longe. As paisagens podem conter arquitetura ou figuras, mas o foco principal continua sendo a terra. Quando um oceano, mar ou outra grande massa de água dominar a imagem, use "paisagens marinhas". Para áreas reais de terra, em vez de representações, use "paisagens (ambientes)." </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000316/CVAA-BR</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109633/CVAA-BR Consortium (2020-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
